verbose_text: Our data open the discussion on the involvement of the SATB1 / F-actin functional complex in the architecture of the cell nucleus of cells undergoing active cell death and put forward several issues that need be resolved in future studies : i) the issue of which genes are transcribed by this complex; ii) the significance of the cooperation between F-actin and SATB1 in the regulation of active cell death processes; and iii) the role of F-actin in processes regulated by SATB1.
